### RULE 2: Expression Language Injection — CWE-917

**BAD — User input evaluated as expressions:**
```
// Spring SpEL
parser.parseExpression(user_input).getValue()

// OGNL (Struts)
OgnlUtil.getValue(user_input, context, root)

// MVEL
MVEL.eval(user_input)

// JEXL
jexl.createExpression(user_input).evaluate(context)

// JavaScript
eval(user_input)
new Function(user_input)()
vm.runInContext(user_input, context)
setTimeout(user_input, 0)                       // String argument = eval
```

**GOOD — Never evaluate user-controlled expressions:**
```
// Use allowlisted operations
ALLOWED_FIELDS = {"name", "email", "age"}
IF user_input IN ALLOWED_FIELDS:
    value = object.getProperty(user_input)      // Property access, not expression eval

// If expression evaluation is required, use a sandboxed evaluator
// with no access to runtime classes
SpelParserConfiguration config = new SpelParserConfiguration(
    SpelCompilerMode.OFF, null     // Disable compilation
);
// AND restrict available types/methods via TypeLocator
```

**Also check for:**
- Spring `@Value("${...}")` with user-controlled property sources
- OGNL injection in Struts (you've analyzed CVE-2025-64775 — this is the family)
- Log4j-style JNDI lookup strings (`${jndi:ldap://...}`) in any string evaluation context

