### RULE 3: LDAP Injection — CWE-90

**BAD — User input in LDAP filters:**
```
filter = "(uid=" + username + ")"                        // No escaping
filter = "(&(uid=" + user + ")(userPassword=" + pass + "))"  // Auth bypass
// Attack: username = "*)(uid=*))(|(uid=*"
// Result: Filter becomes always-true, bypasses authentication
```

**GOOD — Escape LDAP special characters:**
```
FUNCTION ldap_escape(input):
    // Escape: * ( ) \ NUL
    result = input.replace("\\", "\\5c")
    result = result.replace("*", "\\2a")
    result = result.replace("(", "\\28")
    result = result.replace(")", "\\29")
    result = result.replace("\0", "\\00")
    RETURN result

filter = "(uid=" + ldap_escape(username) + ")"

// Or use framework-provided filter builders
filter = Filter.equals("uid", username)          // Parameterized
```

**Also check for:**
- DN (Distinguished Name) injection — different escaping rules than filter strings
- LDAP injection in Active Directory queries (common in enterprise Java)

