### RULE 4: HTTP Header Injection — CWE-113

**BAD — User input in response headers:**
```
response.setHeader("Location", user_input)        // Open redirect
response.setHeader("X-Custom", user_input)        // CRLF injection
// Attack: user_input = "value\r\nSet-Cookie: admin=true"
// Result: Response splitting — attacker injects arbitrary headers

// Email header injection
mail.addHeader("To", user_email)
// Attack: user_email = "victim@example.com\r\nBCC: attacker@evil.com"
```

**GOOD — Validate and strip control characters:**
```
FUNCTION safe_header_value(input):
    IF input.contains("\r") OR input.contains("\n"):
        THROW Error("Invalid header value")
    RETURN input

// Redirect: allowlist targets
ALLOWED_REDIRECTS = {"/dashboard", "/profile", "/home"}
IF redirect_target IN ALLOWED_REDIRECTS:
    response.redirect(redirect_target)
ELSE:
    response.redirect("/home")   // Default safe redirect
```

